📘 UNIQA RFP – Final Memory Jogger (Strictly Based on PPT + Emails + Our Discussion)
1️⃣ What the PPT Contains (Exact Content Only)
1.1 Overall Context
UNIQA Insurance Group issued an RFP to build three AI MVPs, each with a 3‑month duration, starting July 2026, with proposal submission due 10 April 2026.

The PPT defines three MVPs:

MVP 1 – Claims Processing Automation
Problems Identified (from PPT)
Early-stage claims processing is manual and slow.

Email-based submissions require human triage.

Data enrichment and routing are inconsistent.

Need for controlled automation with human oversight.

What the PPT Requests
AI-supported automation for early-stage claims.

Three use cases:

Legal Protection (Consultation Insurance)

Car Casco Claim Registration

MTPL Recourse Detection

Email intake → AI understanding → enrichment → routing → claim creation/update.

Human-in-the-loop escalation.

Integration with claims backend systems.

End-to-end auditability.

Compliance with security, data protection, regulatory requirements.

Modular, extensible design.

Deployment on Microsoft Azure.

MVP 2 – Corporate Underwriting Assistant
Problems Identified (from PPT)
Underwriters lack fast, AI-supported decision tools.

Risk assessment requires data from multiple systems.

No unified knowledge representation.

What the PPT Requests
AI-powered Underwriting Assistant.

Integrations with:

CBN

Inquiry Manager

Large Loss Database

GEAM

Google Maps

Knowledge Graph for risk-related data.

AI agents for:

Risk assessment

Compliance checks

Wording comparison

Human-in-the-loop feedback loop.

Underwriter Decision Dashboard.

Data provenance, explainability, auditability.

Security, privacy, compliance.

Scalable Azure-based architecture.

Training and support for underwriters and IT teams.

MVP 3 – Agentic AI Platform
Problems Identified (from PPT)
UNIQA lacks a unified, governed AI platform.

Need for reusable, scalable AI capabilities across countries.

What the PPT Requests
Group-level AI platform with:

Shared core model

Country-specific integrations

Integration with enterprise systems:

Identity & Access Management

Data platforms

BPM/workflow platforms

Standardized tool registration + secure API invocation.

Controlled knowledge ingestion, retrieval, storage.

Model abstraction layer for approved model providers.

Governance layer:

Policy enforcement

Content filtering

Audit logging

Observability + monitoring (logging, metrics, alerting).

Horizontal scalability + high availability.

Developer enablement framework (templates, SDKs).

Co-build model with structured knowledge transfer.

Compliance with enterprise architecture + security policies.

MVP platform focused on claims + underwriting use cases.

