4️⃣ Our Discussion Conclusions (Only What We Agreed On)
4.1 Understanding the Three MVPs
MVP 1 = Operational automation (claims).

MVP 2 = Decision intelligence (underwriting).

MVP 3 = Foundational AI platform (agentic + governed).

4.2 Relationship Between MVPs
MVP1 and MVP2 are use cases.

MVP3 is the platform that will eventually host and scale these use cases.

MVP3 must be designed with MVP1 and MVP2 as first tenants.

4.3 Your Actual Role
You are not building the MVPs.
You are designing the plan for how they will be built.

Your deliverables include:

Solution architecture for each MVP

Effort estimation

Delivery timeline

Team structure

Risks & assumptions

Integration approach

Azure architecture (because PPT explicitly requires Azure)

Governance & compliance approach

Human-in-the-loop design

Knowledge graph design (for MVP2)

Agentic platform blueprint (for MVP3)

4.4 Clarifications We Agreed On
No OCR mentioned in PPT

No confidence scoring mentioned

No extraction pipelines mentioned

No backend orchestration details mentioned

Only conceptual routing mentioned

Azure is explicitly required

Human-in-the-loop is explicitly required

AI agents are explicitly required

Knowledge graph is explicitly required

